<div class="main" id="library">
<h2>Libraries</h2>
  <div id="libDiv">
    <p>Once, I was a librarian.</p> 

    <p>I have a degree in library science and I spent a few years manning the reference desk at a public library. I haven't thought about going back for a long time.  Now, though, I'm not ruling it out.</p>

    <p>Some of the most impressive, interesting and useful work happening in libraries really happening online. To have the technical ability parse vast amounts of information, to connect disparate forms and formats, to make something useful: It would definitely be worth while.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="main" id="kids">
  
    <h2>Kids</h2>
  
  <div id="kidContent">
    <img src="photos/kids1.jpg" alt="Niece and Nephews">
    <div id="kidCaption">
      <p>Yes, they are cute.  My niece and nephews, from left to right: Jasper, Asa, Carys, and Shepard.  I gladly spend a lot of time with them.</p>

      <p>I'm eager to turn them into my own private focus group. What could I make specifically for them? What would educate or entertain? What kind of UI would a four-year-old possibly respond to? Really, though, what are the information needs of an eight-year-old?   
      </p>

      <p>One simple idea, that could make for a good exercise: Create an interface that makes it easy for them to find videos.</p> 

      <p>Watching YouTube videos on Mom and Dad's iPad is, from what I've seen, the only way that they make use of the internet. What if they could 'click' on a large Barbie button to perform a pre-programmed search for Barbie? I might be on to something.</p>
    </div>  
